========================================================================
HOW THIS ALPHABET EVOLVES — REALITY BREAKS IT, NOT AUTHORITY
========================================================================

  v0.1 of this empire alphabet had a `needs-dan-review` flag asking Dan
  to correct entries by hand. Dan's response: 'or reality breaks it better?'

  he was right. authority is fragile. reality isn't. so v0.2 changed the
  selection pressure:

    · primitives are not 'documented / inferred / needs-dan-review'.
      they are 'untested' until composition pressure tests them.
    · every time a primitive is composed in a real build, the outcome is
      logged: worked / partial / broke. confidence is DERIVED, not declared.
    · primitives that survive many compositions earn high confidence.
      primitives that break across multiple composition contexts get pruned.
    · the alphabet pins a new CID after every test outcome — the lineage
      is a record of what reality killed and what reality kept.

  Dan does not have to read these entries and correct them. Dan composes
  with them. when his next build uses 'biscuit_economy + cortex + d4d',
  the build either ships or it doesn't. if it ships, all three primitives'
  reality_tests get a 'worked' entry. if it breaks, the broken primitive
  gets a 'broke' entry — and either dies or mutates.

